main event: A UFO report concerning the analysis of a submitted specimen that struck a boy's balloon on August 25, 1967.
interesting points: The object was not officially submitted as a UFO report, but for analysis of the specimen only., The report details the analysis of a specimen identified as coke, with no evidence of extraterrestrial origins., The specimen was submitted by a witness who contacted this office., The analysis was conducted by the Air Force Materials Laboratory Identification Section., The initial observation mentioned a saucer-like object in 1950.
witness description: a young boy who had a balloon struck by the object
